Locked(uint256).details: If a token is minted and the status is locked, this event should be emitted.

Unlocked(uint256).details: If a token is minted and the status is unlocked, this event should be emitted.

burn(uint256).details: Burns `tokenId`. See {ERC721-_burn}. Requirements: - The caller must own `tokenId` or be an approved operator.

locked(uint256).details: SBTs assigned to zero address are considered invalid, and queries about them do throw.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

Locked(uint256).notice: Emitted when the locking status is changed to locked.

Unlocked(uint256).notice: Emitted when the locking status is changed to unlocked.currently SBT Contract does not emit Unlocked event

locked(uint256).notice: Returns the locking status of an Soulbound Token
